### ============================================================
### Mini CRM de Contatos — API Tests
### ============================================================
### Prerequisites:
###   1. Run `php artisan migrate:fresh --seed`
###   2. Run `php artisan serve` (starts at http://localhost:8000)
###   3. For score processing to actually execute:
###      Run `php artisan queue:work` in another terminal
###      (queue driver is "database" — jobs persist to DB)
###
### How to use: Click "Send Request" above any request block.
### Variables (@baseUrl) set below — change port if needed.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api

### ============================================================
### CONTACTS — CRUD
### ============================================================

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 1. List Contacts (empty initially)
### Returns 200 with paginated list (data: [], meta: {...})
### ----------------------------------------------------------

GET {{baseUrl}}/contacts

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 2. Create Contact — minimum valid payload
### Returns 201
### Expected: status = "pending", score = 0
### ----------------------------------------------------------

POST {{baseUrl}}/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "João Silva",
    "email": "joao@gmail.com",
    "phone": "11988888888"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 3. Create Contact — corporate email (will score higher)
### Returns 201
### This contact: corporate (+20) + multi-word (+10) + SP DDD (+20) = score 50
### ----------------------------------------------------------

POST {{baseUrl}}/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Maria Souza",
    "email": "maria@company.com",
    "phone": "11999999999"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 4. Create Contact — .br email + other state DDD
### Returns 201
### This contact: .br TLD (+10) + corporate (+20) + multi-word (+10) + other DDD (+10) = 50
### ----------------------------------------------------------

POST {{baseUrl}}/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Ana Oliveira",
    "email": "ana@empresa.com.br",
    "phone": "21988888888"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 5. Create Contact — single name + invalid DDD
### Returns 201
### This contact: single word name (+0) + DDD < 11 (+0) = score 0
### ----------------------------------------------------------

POST {{baseUrl}}/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Carlos",
    "email": "carlos@hotmail.com",
    "phone": "10999999999"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 6. Create Contact — validation errors
### Returns 422 with validation messages
### ----------------------------------------------------------

POST {{baseUrl}}/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "",
    "email": "invalid-email",
    "phone": ""
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 7. Create Contact — duplicate email
### Returns 422
### ----------------------------------------------------------

POST {{baseUrl}}/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Jose Duplicate",
    "email": "joao@gmail.com",
    "phone": "21977777777"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 8. Show a Contact (use id from a created contact)
### Returns 200 with full contact JSON
### ----------------------------------------------------------

GET {{baseUrl}}/contacts/1

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 9. Show non-existent Contact
### Returns 404
### ----------------------------------------------------------

GET {{baseUrl}}/contacts/9999

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 10. Update Contact
### Returns 200 with updated data
### ----------------------------------------------------------

PUT {{baseUrl}}/contacts/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "João Souza Updated",
    "phone": "21988888888"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 11. Update Contact — validation errors
### Returns 422
### ----------------------------------------------------------

PUT {{baseUrl}}/contacts/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "",
    "email": "bad-email"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 12. Delete Contact (soft delete)
### Returns 204
### After this, GET /contacts/1 returns 404
### ----------------------------------------------------------

DELETE {{baseUrl}}/contacts/1

### ============================================================
### SCORE PROCESSING
### ============================================================

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 13. Trigger Score Processing
### Returns 202 (accepted — job queued)
### ----------------------------------------------------------

POST {{baseUrl}}/contacts/2/process-score

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 14. Trigger Score Processing — non-existent contact
### Returns 404
### ----------------------------------------------------------

POST {{baseUrl}}/contacts/9999/process-score

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 15. Verify Score After Processing
### If queue worker is running (php artisan queue:work),
### the contact's status should be "active" and score calculated.
### Contact 2 (Maria Souza): corporate +20, multi-word +10, SP DDD +20 = 50
### Contact 3 (Ana Oliveira): corporate +20, .br TLD +10, multi-word +10, other DDD +10 = 50
### Contact 4 (Carlos): hotmail (+0), single word (+0), DDD 10 (+0) = 0
### ----------------------------------------------------------

GET {{baseUrl}}/contacts/2
GET {{baseUrl}}/contacts/3
GET {{baseUrl}}/contacts/4

### ----------------------------------------------------------
### 16. Trigger Score Processing — already processed contact
### Returns 202 (job queued). Job will fail because
### status machine rejects "active → processing" transition.
### ----------------------------------------------------------

POST {{baseUrl}}/contacts/2/process-score

### ============================================================
### SCORING RULES REFERENCE
### ============================================================
### Email Domain:
###   - Corporate (not gmail/hotmail/yahoo) → +20
###   - .br TLD → +10
###
### Name Length:
###   - Multi-word (≥2 words) → +10
###   - Single word → 0
###
### Phone DDD:
###   - 11–19 (São Paulo) → +20
###   - 20+ (other state) → +10
###   - < 11 (invalid) → 0
###
### Status Machine:
###   pending → processing → active | failed
###
### Queue:
###   - Driver: database
###   - Job sleeps 1-2 seconds to simulate work
###   - $tries = 1 (no infinite retries)
